-- Harlequins, Toulon, Clermont Qualify for Heineken Cup Quarters
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-01-12T20:12:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-12/harlequins-toulon-clermont-qualify-for-heineken-cup-quarters.html
Harlequins, Toulon and Clermont
Auvergne maintained their perfect records after five matches to
qualify for the Heineken Cup rugby quarterfinals.  Harlequins routed Connact 48-7 in Pool 3, Toulon beat
 Cardiff Blues  45-25 to qualify from Pool 6 and Clermont won Pool
5 with a 46-3 win over Exeter. The six pool winners and two best
second-place teams after six games advance to the knockout
rounds of  Europe ’s elite club competition.  Defending champion Leinster beat the Scarlets 33-14 to stay
alive in Pool 5, Saracens beat Racing Metro 37-28 to lead Pool 1
and Biarretz remained second in Pool 3 with a 32-6 win over
Zebre.  Ultser, last season’s runner-up, became the first team to
reach the quarterfinals by beating Glasgow 23-6 last night in
Pool 4.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  